+# Simulation Toolkit AI - Refactoring%0A%0AThis document outlines the major refactoring changes made to the Simulation Toolkit AI codebase.%0A%0A## Core Architecture Changes%0A%0A### 1. Brain System%0A- Added a %60Brain%60 abstract class as the base for all decision-making components%0A- Implemented %60HumanBrain%60 for player-controlled entities%0A- Implemented %60AIBrain%60 for AI-controlled entities%0A- Moved awareness from Entity to Brain for better encapsulation%0A%0A### 2. Entity Hierarchy%0A- Maintained %60Entity%60 as the base class for all entities%0A- Added %60Character%60 as an intermediate class with health, combat abilities%0A- Updated %60Player%60 to inherit from %60Character%60 instead of directly from %60Entity%60%0A- Characters now have a Brain that controls their decision-making%0A%0A### 3. Configuration System%0A- Added %60MatchConfig%60 for loading simulation settings from JSON or XML%0A- Added %60AgentConfig%60 for configuring individual agents%0A- Support for different brain types (Human/AI)%0A- Support for different simulation modes (Realtime/Offline)%0A%0A### 4. Simulation System%0A- Added %60Simulation%60 class to manage the simulation lifecycle%0A- Support for Realtime and Offline simulation modes%0A- Event-based architecture for simulation events%0A- Proper separation of simulation logic from visualization%0A%0A### 5. Unity Integration%0A- Added %60AIToolkitRunner%60 MonoBehaviour for Unity integration%0A- Support for loading configuration files in Unity%0A- Visualization of entities in Unity%0A- Input handling for human-controlled entities%0A%0A### 6. Console Application%0A- Added %60ConsoleRunner%60 for running simulations from the command line%0A- Support for loading configuration files%0A- Proper error handling and validation%0A- Output of simulation results%0A%0A## Key Benefits%0A%0A1. **Separation of Concerns**%0A - Clear separation between simulation logic and visualization%0A - Brain handles decision-making, Character handles state, Entity handles basic properties%0A%0A2. **Flexibility**%0A - Support for different brain types allows for both human and AI control%0A - Configuration system allows for easy setup of different simulations%0A - Simulation modes support both interactive and batch processing%0A%0A3. **Extensibility**%0A - Easy to add new brain types%0A - Easy to add new entity types%0A - Easy to add new simulation features%0A%0A4. **Maintainability**%0A - Clear class hierarchy%0A - Well-defined responsibilities%0A - Proper encapsulation%0A%0A## Usage Examples%0A%0A### Console Application%0A%60%60%60csharp%0A// Load a configuration file%0Avar config = MatchConfig.LoadFromFile(%22sample_config.json%22);%0A%0A// Create a simulation in offline mode%0Avar simulation = new Simulation(config, SimulationMode.Offline);%0A%0A// Initialize and run the simulation%0Asimulation.Initialize();%0Asimulation.Start();%0A%60%60%60%0A%0A### Unity Integration%0A%60%60%60csharp%0A// In a MonoBehaviour%0Apublic void StartSimulation(string configPath)%0A%7B%0A // Load the configuration%0A var config = MatchConfig.LoadFromFile(configPath);%0A %0A // Create the simulation%0A var simulation = new Simulation(config, SimulationMode.Realtime);%0A %0A // Initialize and start the simulation%0A simulation.Initialize();%0A simulation.Start();%0A %0A // Process input for a human-controlled player%0A simulation.ProcessPlayerInput(playerId, Direction.Up, true);%0A%7D%0A%60%60%60%0A%0A## Configuration Example%0A%60%60%60json%0A%7B%0A %22Name%22: %22Sample Match%22,%0A %22MapPath%22: %22maps/default.txt%22,%0A %22RealtimeMode%22: true,%0A %22MaxSteps%22: 1000,%0A %22Agents%22: %5B%0A %7B%0A %22Name%22: %22Player%22,%0A %22BrainType%22: %22Human%22,%0A %22RandomStart%22: true,%0A %22Awareness%22: 15,%0A %22MaxHealth%22: 100,%0A %22AttackPower%22: 10,%0A %22Defense%22: 5,%0A %22Speed%22: 1.0%0A %7D,%0A %7B%0A %22Name%22: %22Enemy1%22,%0A %22BrainType%22: %22AI%22,%0A %22RandomStart%22: true,%0A %22Awareness%22: 8,%0A %22Max